  By now, it is known that the new silo, Squared, will be introduced in 1H 2026. Initial offering will be a single racket, targeting broad audience: beginner/intermediate, tennis coaches, doubles players.
  
  Yes, the frame is super versatile:
  
  \- it is light, low SW, headlight. Yet…
  
  \- it is super stable in the stock form. I am not sure how they did it but I, and those that tried it, are very pleasantly surprised by its stability.
  
  \- it is a very comfortable frame, yet offers easy power, spun and again, surprising control.
  
  Some teasing frames are circulating around and we have seen some shots of what may be the final paint job of the frame (I have seen the final PJ in person and it looks great).
  
  I am starting this thread to build awareness, and to get those that had a chance to test it inputs, feedbacks and curious To hear if their experience matches mine.
  
