  ## Description
  
  ```
  HEAD have just released one of the most unusual rackets we have seen in years. At first glance the HEAD Squared looks familiar, but there is something fundamentally different about the way this frame is designed and how it behaves on court.
  
  In this video we take a closer look at what might be the most interesting racket launch of the year. The Squared concept challenges some long held assumptions about racket geometry, sweet spot behaviour and how a frame should interact with the ball. It raises a lot of questions about whether small design changes can create a completely different hitting experience.
  
  But the real story only appears once you start hitting with it. There is a very specific type of player this racket seems to target, and the way it performs might surprise people who think they already understand what modern rackets are supposed to feel like.
  
  If you are curious about where racket design might be heading next, the HEAD Squared is a release that demands attention. In this video we explore what makes it so unusual and why it could end up being one of the most talked about rackets of the year.
  
